subSubSection.paragraph:
Cephalothorax
(
Fig. 11A–C
): Carapace yellowish, long oval, widest at coxae II and III; with a large deep yellow pattern (both lateral margins of pattern are wavelike lines) between ocular area and fovea, with three longitudinal rows of setae; a pair of brown patches on the lateral margins of carapace near Coxa I; fovea inconspicuous. Sternum yellowish. Labium yellow. Chelicerae (
Fig. 15C, D
) deep yellow, with six promarginal peg teeth and two retromarginal teeth. Endites deep yellow, longer than wide. Leg color similar to carapace, with irregular dark brown blotches.

